    <exprreq message="Power Attack feat required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fPowerAtt] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="aS2BrutFig" name="Brute Fighting" description="Your extensive training with two-handed weapons is revealed through brutally effective tactics.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Warforged, Str 13, Power Attack, base attack bonus +3.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Brute Fighting enables the use of three tactical maneuvers.\n\n{i}Combat Momentum:{/i} If you deal damage to a foe with a charge attack made with a two-handed weapon and that opponent then fails to hit you before your next turn, you gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls against that opponent on your next turn.\n\n{i}Dispatch the Fallen:{/i} If you successfully bull rush or overrun a foe, any melee attack you make against that foe with a two-handed weapon on your next turn gains a +4 bonus on damage rolls.\n\n{i}Frenzied Attack:{/i} If you hit a foe with a two-handed weapon at least once on two consecutive turns during which you use the Power Attack feat (taking at least a â€“2 penalty on attack rolls), you gain a +2 bonus on all attack rolls you make with that weapon against the same foe for the rest of the round." compset="Ability" summary="3 special manuevers: Combat Momentum, Dispatch the Fallen &amp; Frenzied Attack." uniqueness="useronce">
