  <thing id="fS2ConLock" name="Construct Lock" description="Your knowledge of construct nature allows you to deal extra damage to or even immobilize such foes.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Warforged, base attack bonus +2.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against creatures with the construct type (including living constructs).\n\nIf you roll a critical threat against a construct, you can forego the confirmation roll to make another attack roll using the same modifier. If this second attack also hits and deals at least 1 point of damage, the construct must succeed on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Con modifier) or be rendered immobile and helpless for 1 round (as if it had been paralyzed).\n\n{b}Special:{/b} If you spend an action point to improve an attack roll against a construct and hit with the attack, the attack roll is automatically considered to be a critical threat regardless of the number rolled on the die." compset="Feat" summary="Don&apos;t crit to make 2nd attack. If successfull make a Fort save or be Paralyzed." uniqueness="useronce">
